      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That feeling of losing a part of yourself is agonizing, and it makes perfect sense that the world feels alien when your own world has stopped. The ache you feel is a testament to the depth of the connection you lost, and it's a profound pain to carry. Please consider talking to a grief counselor or therapist; they are trained to help you navigate this specific kind of hollow feeling.",
      "source": "target",
